[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring dynamic coverage**\n\nI'm considering how dynamic coverage works with native compilation, especially concerning mapping call sites to tests that can run under native. It seems like I could avoid the MissingReflectionRegistrationError by not directly using JAXPDOMAdapter under native. But that might impact coverage, which is something I want to avoid altering. I should focus on the active class and maybe add a test to run through JDOM's DOMOutputter default adapter instead, which would invoke the JAXPDOMAdapter without needing a direct new instance. Time to inspect DOMOutputter!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_02d2ee91448a4a000169fc7d9379b4819c9952fca2a3028b7e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_H2czAgDBkcuk5lPlgchqBCqld5MBPi3LA1sZLyUAHgUm8ekMCxFwH8X7eBApdLdOmEPjfcOvzoJeIKyTp__4u2HZQ2WPGHEGP4lsvMCl0djgToSL96ccdAbVwVbs6X5xnY4W0w7f-8fdbiD1wHT8daoX8XBtEuTBSBilEwIbdkvv1yjLKGV8ze5LvOm4MUIVBF7vxl2aH2rSY-Fm39P12JSsZoSNWol1FBTLDtv0aCUpJ7nBr2qqYiDe8ZEeDasDvy3K4k5BPSGyeIbjc9UxeortdsgPUcS-rem8_ziU5dXxj0KTZuceJlAFR0x5fhIdyQWVOjg5o27Fph71p8hJH-x7RvqVSHzBmqvFON_dGJnjYQlshR1Am-3BKkorjCMC1wLwN4ZJkmAXS5KVMSC1qkF499qKcYlIKaJn5seGKfH45r_0tbeyl93TlcxozB3SFdYtRHLBpUwdtq0dQzU1BBT2Z6VkPeh3rUnY3-AQ64eeaZnVckWCEo5L9-1bGsE3VdHUNdVHe5G54-XvYTbcD_b2bTE_Z_790bWjyxRzo9tashWKjmZPTWrr8cyV1fNAJC5DFx8lyGWIGIxuSTUOlYAm6f1wkVkYCvHnzu-vHB-sMstWuSiBfdoW7m9mFh8UL5a4xitSyGOPJSViilwmf02neUbvuYBvw6XOrp6iYDBT3HF1324R9JLPgi_nfq1u0vjrbNC0DjKGpVrBFroV2FCynaHJUvNtJByQ23-KB_8BklXNFkCGct5c4ImhtpVlHnz1EIyjqtom9vSP-MFaj6LVQQ32lLPmxwgpqcQ88qxzHKRE3pdPsMXeAAdJl4Br2ziLeizYD5a4IJTLz7emJlwestyDzbNlQtavwuOpc-t7gzLWxveXiiWidBgClYYJ-GIrhKNLRsSdNGCywcCV5qCiidV2WQySaNd-9LJEs6V_N4Txf5tIngcx-ic3O03AQcXioo5AJOr1nIO09Jy397_OsbQkttWxaiLLBbk6IB95JA8orlt0FIoPRH1xAp64rsFIKdLGrhMRHZoqzf1XDFfXaFv3iLuk-IYpp0Tu8tbzMNrZoRlb9H_ISyibWYH1CNbKWkwh1ZXJVicfAMlU-0BlGKnHUMyI6JPrUB4y6YUslc0BLBNyZXlXNPRhmg